# Rewrite every non-empty sender (envelope MAIL FROM + From: header) to the
# single SES-verified identity. Installed to /etc/postfix/sender_canonical.regexp
# by setup.sh; referenced from main.cf via sender_canonical_maps.
#
# /.+/ deliberately does NOT match the null sender <>, so bounce / NDR messages
# keep their empty return-path and cannot loop into a backscatter storm (which a
# `static:` map would cause by rewriting <> to a deliverable address).
/.+/    scanner@samirgroup.com
